perfect-banner
==============

Your python project might have a cool looking
ascii art banner. But did you thought, that
some users may have a terminal open which has
a character width that is smaller than the one
of the art.

Perhaps you want create multiple banners with
different sizes so users with a smaller terminal
can take a look at your wonderful

```
  ____                              
 |  _ \                             
 | |_) | __ _ _ __  _ __   ___ _ __ 
 |  _ < / _` | '_ \| '_ \ / _ \ '__|
 | |_) | (_| | | | | | | |  __/ |   
 |____/ \__,_|_| |_|_| |_|\___|_|   
                                    
```


Installation
------------


```
pip install perfect-banner
```


Example Usage
-------------


```python
import banner
import art

def get_banners():
    for font in art.FONT_NAMES:
        yield art.text2art("python", font)

choice = banner.choose(*get_banners())
print(choice)
```


